#X text 70 25 In this section we have Ring Modulated synths and we start by applying Ring Modulation to a set of sine waves. Hence \, we're combining the idea of Additive Synthesis with Ring Modulation. Before \, we were doing a Low Frequency Ring Modulation with Additive Synthesis \, which did produce slow gain/amplitude variations for each partials. Now we have each partial Ring Modulated., f 78;
#X text 322 427 As an excercize \, you can create a polyphonic synth with this idea and add Low Frequency Ring Modulation as well as Low Frequency Pitch variations., f 33;
#X text 324 227 The partials are randomly placed an octave up or below the pitch input. The modulation frequencies are also random for each partial. We're combining triangular waves \, which produce a richer sound., f 34;
